UPDATE `broadcast_text` SET `MaleText`='Check it out here, got the best seats in the house!\n\nDid you come here to watch some fights, too?', `VerifiedBuild`=19831 WHERE `ID`=84251; -- 84251
UPDATE `broadcast_text` SET `FemaleText`='Did the boss send you?\n\nLook, if he asks, just tell him I''m doing some underwater excavation.', `VerifiedBuild`=19831 WHERE `ID`=84529; -- 84529
UPDATE `broadcast_text` SET `MaleText`='These Warsong guys couldn''t possibly need all of the supplies they''ve been stockpiling here - especially after the Horde puts the hurt on ''em. \n\nSo the way I see it, if we want to take some to make some profit on the side, what''s the harm?', `VerifiedBuild`=19831 WHERE `ID`=84604; -- 84604
UPDATE `broadcast_text` SET `MaleText`='She''s nothing now, a twisted soul chained to our world.  My sister was so sweet, so loving, so young... The Shadowmoon did this!  Twisted her by some foul magic! They left her walking the world as a shadow, crying out in eternal torment.\n\nI couldn''t.  I can''t.  I cannot end her pain.  I cannot be the one to relive her pain.\n\nRelease her spirit.  Put her to rest.  I cannot bear seeing her like this.', `VerifiedBuild`=19831 WHERE `ID`=84628; -- 84628
UPDATE `broadcast_text` SET `MaleText`='So you''ve done it?  Well, then.  Be gone and leave me to my mourning.\n\nSo young... she was so young...', `VerifiedBuild`=19831 WHERE `ID`=84629; -- 84629
UPDATE `broadcast_text` SET `FemaleText`='Greetings, commander! My name is Rangari Chel.$b$bWhen we first arrived on Draenor, this whole world was a mystery - a dangerous mystery. The rangari were tasked with exploring all these new, hostile environments. We learned to survive on our feet - using the natural resources of the land around us to survive and slip unseen in and out of enemy territory.$b$bAs your follower, I''d focus on staying out of sight, keeping foes at bay, and doing serious damage.', `VerifiedBuild`=19831 WHERE `ID`=85007; -- 85007
UPDATE `broadcast_text` SET `FemaleText`='Commander, it is a pleasure to meet you.$b$bWhen I was young I trained hard to become an anchorite in the priesthood, but the Light walks us down mysterious paths. My defensive spells were so powerful that the Prophet himself encouraged me to train with the Vindicators.$b$bThese days, I am not afraid to stand toe-to-toe with our enemies, protecting those behind me. Choose me as your follower and my faith will be your shield, my armor a bulwark protecting your garrison from our many enemies.', `VerifiedBuild`=19831 WHERE `ID`=85011; -- 85011
UPDATE `broadcast_text` SET `MaleText`='|TInterface\\\\Icons\\\\sha_ability_rogue_bloodyeye.blp:32|t$b\n|cFFFF0000|Hspell:167410|h[Khadgar''s Watch]|h|r reverses time!', `FemaleText`='|TInterface\\\\Icons\\\\sha_ability_rogue_bloodyeye.blp:32|t$b\n|cFFFF0000|Hspell:167410|h[Khadgar''s Watch]|h|r reverses time!', `VerifiedBuild`=19831 WHERE `ID`=85114; -- 85114
UPDATE `broadcast_text` SET `MaleText`='To prove yourself worthy of the wolf, you must first test your strength and tenacity. \n\nTo do this, you must gather a heavy stone from the quarry and bear it on your back into the lands of your enemy. Once you have cut your way through their ranks, place the stone in a place of prominence, and set upon it a trophy of your foe.\n\nOnly then, when your strength is displayed for all to see, can you hope to claim the wolf as your subject.', `VerifiedBuild`=19831 WHERE `ID`=85330; -- 85330
UPDATE `broadcast_text` SET `MaleText`='Once your display of strength is set for all to see, you must claim your wolf.\n\nGo to their hunting grounds. There you must find the largest wolf in the pack, and subdue it in the presence of its kin. You will likely be eaten alive, but if you survive the ordeal, the wolf will answer to you as its master.', `VerifiedBuild`=19831 WHERE `ID`=85331; -- 85331
UPDATE `broadcast_text` SET `MaleText`='It is not enough that the wolf regard you as its master. To ready your wolf for riding, you must break its will completely.\n\nOnce you have subdued your wolf, you will mount it and ride it to the top of the tallest peak in Nagrand. If your wolf is willful, it will throw you to your death on the mountain slopes. \n\nIf you survive to the peak, the will of your wolf will be broken. \n\nThen, you can call yourself "Wolfrider".', `VerifiedBuild`=19831 WHERE `ID`=85332; -- 85332
UPDATE `broadcast_text` SET `MaleText`='This Warsong orc looks to have died trying to carry a giant stone through the Gorian outpost. \n\nThere''s no clear indication of where he was taking the stone, but it obviously didn''t help him in combat.', `VerifiedBuild`=19831 WHERE `ID`=85395; -- 85395
UPDATE `broadcast_text` SET `MaleText`='Amongst many scribbled entries of the trials of a pirate''s life and a surprising amount of different uses for barnacles, you find an entry of note:\n\n"''Tis been a week since that cursed bird made off with the keys to my chest. He keeps flyin'' by, as if he be tauntin'' me, but I can''t seem to to catch him on the wing. \n\nThat good for nothin'' squab can''t fly forever. I''ll just wait here ''till he goes aground."', `VerifiedBuild`=19831 WHERE `ID`=85533; -- 85533
UPDATE `broadcast_text` SET `FemaleText`='Fellworth got our group lost by finding a "shortcut" through the hollow and now my boots are full of slime and mud!\n\nI think I will be charge of the map from now on.', `VerifiedBuild`=19831 WHERE `ID`=85659; -- 85659
UPDATE `broadcast_text` SET `MaleText`='It bein'' just my luck, mon! I be findin'' da best fishin'' spot down ''ere, but only after da elementals and da ogres broke up all my gear. \n\nNow I''m needin'' a new rod, reel, and da special voodoo lure so I can land da big ones hidin'' in da weeds.', `VerifiedBuild`=19831 WHERE `ID`=85674; -- 85674
